    "explanation": "Because worker pay must be strictly proportional to their quality to maintain fairness, the total payment distributed depends completely on the 'ratio' (`wage / quality`) of the most demanding worker in the group. Any worker with a lower expected ratio will inherently receive more than their minimum wage, satisfying condition 1. Any worker with a higher expected ratio will be underpaid, violating the condition.\nThus, to form a valid group of `k` workers, we must first sort all workers by their ratio (`wage / quality`). We iterate through this sorted list. As we iterate, the current worker's ratio is considered the 'captain' ratio applied to everyone in the current group. Since we want to minimize total cost (`captain_ratio * sum(quality of group)`), we maintain a max-heap of the `quality` sizes of the currently selected group members. If our group exceeds size `k`, we pop the largest quality contributor from the heap. The cost is updated whenever the group size equals `k`.",
    "answer": "def solve(quality, wage, k):\n    import heapq\n    workers = sorted([(w / q, q, w) for q, w in zip(quality, wage)])\n    res = float('inf')\n    qsum = 0\n    heap = []\n    for ratio, q, w in workers:\n        heapq.heappush(heap, -q)\n        qsum += q\n        if len(heap) > k:\n            qsum += heapq.heappop(heap)\n        if len(heap) == k:\n            res = min(res, ratio * qsum)\n    return f\"{res:.5f}\"",
    "boilerplate": {
        "python": "import sys\n\ndef solve(quality, wage, k):\n    # User logic should be written here\n    return 0.0\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    lines = sys.stdin.read().splitlines()\n    if len(lines) >= 3:\n        quality = list(map(int, lines[0].strip().split()))\n        wage = list(map(int, lines[1].strip().split()))\n        k = int(lines[2].strip())\n        print(solve(quality, wage, k))",
        "cpp": "#include <iostream>\n#include <vector>\n#include <sstream>\n#include <iomanip>\nusing namespace std;\n\ndouble solve(vector<int>& quality, vector<int>& wage, int k) {\n    // User logic should be written here\n    return 0.0;\n}\n\nint main() {\n    string lineQ, lineW;\n    if (getline(cin, lineQ) && getline(cin, lineW)) {\n        vector<int> Q, W;\n        int val, k;\n        stringstream ssQ(lineQ), ssW(lineW);\n        while (ssQ >> val) Q.push_back(val);\n        while (ssW >> val) W.push_back(val);\n        if (cin >> k) {\n            cout << fixed << setprecision(5) << solve(Q, W, k) << endl;\n        }\n    }\n    return 0;\n}",
        "java": "import java.util.Scanner;\n\npublic class Main {\n    public static String solve(int[] quality, int[] wage, int k) {\n        // User logic should be written here\n        return \"0.00000\";\n    }\n\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);\n        if (sc.hasNextLine()) {\n            String[] pQ = sc.nextLine().trim().split(\"\\\\s+\");\n            String[] pW = sc.nextLine().trim().split(\"\\\\s+\");\n            int[] Q = new int[pQ.length];\n            int[] W = new int[pW.length];\n            for (int i = 0; i < pQ.length; i++) Q[i] = Integer.parseInt(pQ[i]);\n            for (int i = 0; i < pW.length; i++) W[i] = Integer.parseInt(pW[i]);\n            if (sc.hasNextInt()) {\n                int k = sc.nextInt();\n                System.out.println(solve(Q, W, k));\n            }\n        }\n        sc.close();\n    }\n}",
        "javascript": "const fs = require('fs');\n\nfunction solve(quality, wage, k) {\n    // User logic should be written here\n    return \"0.00000\";\n}\n\nconst input = fs.readFileSync(0, 'utf8').trim().split('\\n');\nif (input.length >= 3) {\n    const Q = input[0].trim().split(/\\s+/).map(Number);\n    const W = input[1].trim().split(/\\s+/).map(Number);\n    const k = parseInt(input[2]);\n    const res = solve(Q, W, k);\n    console.log(isNaN(res) ? res : res.toFixed(5));\n}",
        "c": "#include <stdio.h>\n#include <stdlib.h>\n\ndouble solve(int* quality, int* wage, int n, int k) {\n    // User logic should be written here\n    return 0.0;\n}\n\nint main() {\n    int capacity = 1000;\n    int* Q = (int*)malloc(capacity * sizeof(int));\n    int* W = (int*)malloc(capacity * sizeof(int));\n    int n = 0, k;\n    char c;\n    while (scanf(\"%d\", &Q[n++]) == 1) {\n        if (n == capacity) {\n            capacity *= 2;\n            Q = (int*)realloc(Q, capacity * sizeof(int));\n            W = (int*)realloc(W, capacity * sizeof(int));\n        }\n        c = getchar();\n        if (c == '\\n' || c == EOF) break;\n    }\n    for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) scanf(\"%d\", &W[i]);\n    if (scanf(\"%d\", &k) == 1) {\n        printf(\"%.5f\\n\", solve(Q, W, n, k));\n    }\n    free(Q);\n    free(W);\n    return 0;\n}"
